'''Pyrena''' or '''pyrene''' is the name for the stone within a [[drupe]] or [[drupelet]]. It consists of a [[seed]] surrounded by hard [[endocarp]] tissue.<ref>{{cite book |author1=Beentje, H. |author2=Williamson, J. |year=2010  |title=The Kew Plant Glossary: an Illustrated Dictionary of Plant Terms |publisher=Kew Publishing |location=Royal Botanic Gardens, Kew  }}</ref><ref>{{cite book |author1=Hickey, M. |author2=King, C. |year=2001  |title=The Cambridge Illustrated Glossary of Botanical Terms |publisher=Cambridge University Press   }}</ref>

